          [i, j, v] = find (3 * eye (2))
                 ⇒ i = [ 1; 2 ]
                 ⇒ j = [ 1; 2 ]
                 ⇒ v = [ 3; 3 ]

     If X is a multi-dimensional array of size m x n x p x ..., J contains the column locations as if X was flattened into a two-dimensional matrix of size m x (n + p + ...).

